{"key":"processedPost-9982059","value":{"id":9982059,"first":9981405,"last":9982912,"when":1237234335,"utime":"03/16/09 11:12 PM","content":"You only use lime in the water bath for <i>pasteurizing straw</i>, and then it drains off with the water.&nbsp; Don't lime bulk substrates such as manure or coir, paper, woodchips, sawdust, etc.<br /><br />The pulp you found will probably work OK for oysters, but why pay for what you can get free?&nbsp; Just use old newspapers, cardboard, magazines, etc., that you have laying around or can get from neighbors.&nbsp; My county government recently gave me the key to the recycling bins so I can get newsprint and other paper products anytime I want for free.&nbsp; Sometimes all you have to do is ask.<br /><br />To correct your nomenclature, spawn consists of the cakes or grains you use to start/expand your mycelium.&nbsp; The paper would be your bulk substrate.<br />RR<br /><br /><a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/07-40/135930560-Phone_Book_Shiitake_013a.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/07-40/135930560-thumb_Phone_Book_Shiitake_013a.jpg\"></a> <a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/07-40/135930550-Phone_Book_Oyster_006a.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/07-40/135930550-thumb_Phone_Book_Oyster_006a.jpg\"></a> <a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/07-34/787406648-phonebook_hericium_029a.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/07-34/787406648-thumb_phonebook_hericium_029a.jpg\"></a>","title":"Re: Will this wok as a decent spawn?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}